parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank imploding and leaking can cause fuel to spill onto the pavement while driving, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Thumping noises from under the rear seat of the car while driving
fuel leaking onto the pavement
strong fuel smell near the vehicle
fuel tank imploding and sucking itself inwards
cracking of the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump bolt can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident, especially if it occurs on a busy street or freeway.
symptoms: Engine failure
loss of power
oil pump bolt falls out and into the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water entering the engine can cause hydrolock, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: Engine failure
loss of power
water entering the engine
hydrolock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel system leak can cause a strong odor of gasoline, which can lead to a fire hazard, and potentially cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline when starting the car
fuel and MPH meter moves up and down when turning to the left.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of an accident, and can also lead to premature wear on other vehicle components.
symptoms: Loud clunking noise from the front suspension when driving over bumps
no warning before the noise occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty TPMS can lead to underinflated tires, which can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of an accident, and can also lead to premature wear on the tires.
symptoms: Tires keep losing air
brake light keeps coming on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unidentified noises can be a sign of a underlying problem that can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: Loud rubbing sound when turning to the left.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Smoke in the Cabin
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden appearance of smoke in the cabin can distract the driver, causing a loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents. Additionally, the smoke can be a sign of an electrical fire, which can spread quickly and cause damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the ceiling and dashboard
burning smell inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light circuit board can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake light does not come on
the console indicator confirms the brake light malfunction.
